* Editor's note: This video footage has been blurred to protect the identity of the children in the video. DURBAN - Two teachers at the George Campbell School of Technology in Durban have been suspended pending an investigation into allegations of racism.
	
	Pupils at the school have accused teachers and a School Governing Body member of racism and assault. They claim they have been called monkeys and the K-word. VIDEO: Another school violence video emerges in Richards Bay Classes were suspended last week after pupils protested and demanded action. A video has emerged in which pupils are shown disrupting classes. At a meeting on Sunday, the SGB resolved to enforce suspensions pending a probe. eNCA